{"title":"The New, Aggressive Smokey Ti Broadens Esker Cycles Hardtail Lineup","link":"https://bikerumor.com/the-new-aggressive-smokey-ti-broadens-esker-cycles-hardtail-lineup/","date":1718025315000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-hero.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" alt=\"(Photos/Esker Cycles)\" /></p>\n<p>Like the Hayduke, Lorax, and Jafey, the gang at <a href=\"https://eskercycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Esker Cycles</a> continues to pay homage to the defenders of the wilderness. Their <a href=\"https://eskercycles.com/pages/smokey-ti\" target=\"_blank\">new aggressive hardtail</a> is named the Smokey Ti. And yes, the name is a tribute to the friendly, responsible, ranger hat-wearin’ bear we all grew up with.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-top-tube-logo-e1717708251593.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"996\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-top-tube-logo-e1717708251593.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Smokey Ti Hardtail top tube logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-top-tube-logo-e1717708251593.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-top-tube-logo-e1717708251593-297x231.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-top-tube-logo-e1717708251593-120x93.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-top-tube-logo-e1717708251593-768x598.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Esker Cycles)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Smokeys-shovel.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Smokeys-shovel.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Smokey Ti Hardtail Smokey's shovel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Smokeys-shovel.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Smokeys-shovel-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Smokeys-shovel-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Smokeys-shovel-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Except maybe now he’ll say, “Only <em>you</em> can manual across that rock garden.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Smokey Ti is their “most aggressive hardtail to date”. It’s longer, lower, and slacker. It sports a head tube angle of 64.5 degrees, with geo optimized for a 160mm fork. The frame can also handle tires up to 2.6″ wide.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-descending.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-descending.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Smokey Ti Hardtail descending\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-descending.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-descending-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-descending-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-descending-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-descending-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-descending-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Smokey Ti’s frame was constructed from seamless, butted, and cold-shaped 3/2.5 titanium, delivering a durable yet comfortable ride. Like their other hardtail offerings, the new Smokey Ti also comes with the Portage Dropout System. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-rear-dropout.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-rear-dropout.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Smokey Ti Hardtail rear dropout\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-rear-dropout.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-rear-dropout-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-rear-dropout-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-rear-dropout-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-tire-clearance.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-tire-clearance.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Smokey Ti Hardtail tire clearance\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-tire-clearance.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-tire-clearance-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-tire-clearance-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-tire-clearance-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\\This allows the rider to run the bike geared or as a singlespeed. Plus, you can use the dropouts to adjust the chainstay length. The dropout system has been <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/esker-portage-dropouts-sram-udh-how-to-add-transmission-hayduke-or-japhy/\">updated with a Universal Derailleur Hanger </a>(UDH).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-on-the-rocks.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-on-the-rocks.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Smokey Ti Hardtail on the rocks\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-on-the-rocks.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-on-the-rocks-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-on-the-rocks-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-on-the-rocks-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-on-the-rocks-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-on-the-rocks-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Geometry and Frame Details</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-geo-chart.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"984\" height=\"1172\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-geo-chart.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Smokey Ti Hardtail geo chart\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-geo-chart.jpeg 984w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-geo-chart-252x300.jpeg 252w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-geo-chart-101x120.jpeg 101w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-geo-chart-768x915.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-frameset.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"849\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-frameset.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Smokey Ti Hardtail frameset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-frameset.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-frameset-297x197.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-frameset-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-frameset-768x509.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Esker Cycles says that even though the Smokey Ti is the most aggressive hardtail they’ve ever made, it’s still an Esker. Meaning they’ve prioritized durability and ease of maintenance. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Unique-chainstay-yoke.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1083\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Unique-chainstay-yoke.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Smokey Ti Hardtail Unique chainstay yoke\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Unique-chainstay-yoke.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Unique-chainstay-yoke-297x251.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Unique-chainstay-yoke-120x102.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Unique-chainstay-yoke-768x650.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-meticulous-welds.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-meticulous-welds.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Smokey Ti Hardtail meticulous welds\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-meticulous-welds.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-meticulous-welds-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-meticulous-welds-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-meticulous-welds-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It utilizes external routing, a threaded bottom bracket, and a 44mm headtube. It uses four different water bottle and accessory mounting positions, which include a 3-pack mount on the downtube for a little extra carrying capacity.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Shralpy-air.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Shralpy-air.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Smokey Ti Hardtail Shralpy air\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Shralpy-air.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Shralpy-air-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Shralpy-air-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Shralpy-air-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Shralpy-air-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-Shralpy-air-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Esker Smokey Ti Pricing</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-full-bike-e1717708624125.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"759\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-full-bike-e1717708624125.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Smokey Ti Hardtail full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-full-bike-e1717708624125.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-full-bike-e1717708624125-297x176.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-full-bike-e1717708624125-120x71.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Esker-Smokey-Ti-Hardtail-full-bike-e1717708624125-768x455.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Frame Only: $2500</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Frame + Fork: Starting at $3100</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Complete Builds: Starting at $4500, with numerous upgrade options available.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Complete Single Speed builds start at $4200</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://eskercycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">EskerCycles.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/the-new-aggressive-smokey-ti-broadens-esker-cycles-hardtail-lineup/\">The New, Aggressive Smokey Ti Broadens Esker Cycles Hardtail Lineup</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"01214064c6439ef87aa2429e9a25d6b766303f1a733fe72d9f15e400e721ac77","category":"Cycling"}